Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe and US Vice President Mike Pence held a meeting in Tokyo to discuss the strengthening of the US-Japan alliance. Pence praised the relationship between the two countries and emphasized the importance of security in the Indo-Pacific region. He expressed gratitude for Japan's commitment to the alliance and discussed plans to provide Japan with additional defense systems. Pence also addressed the issue of North Korea, calling it the most dangerous threat in the region, and announced that the US will soon impose the toughest economic sanctions ever on North Korea. He emphasized the need for vigilance and resolve in dealing with the regime. Both leaders expressed their commitment to standing together as allies and friends.